<Base title="Process Analysis" description="Process analysis of functionality in online shops – Hob by Horse.">
<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">Strategy</p>
<h1>Process Analysis of Functionality in Online Shops</h1>
<p>Faster, more attractive, simpler are success criteria in e-commerce for the functionality of an online shop. With process analysis, we make visible how well these and other criteria are fulfilled. On the basis of the analysis results, we develop improvements tailored to your business model and the requirements of your target group.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Careful Process Analysis by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>The term process analysis describes the systematic breakdown of all processes in the online shop into individual parts. Each element is tested in its current functionality and evaluated for weaknesses. Improvements are faster and easier to implement at such a split-down scale than in the overall complex. A reason for the analysis can be an existing online shop that has not been updated for a long time. Methodical approach and the right tools for improvements characterise our work for your e-commerce.</p>
<h2>Strategic Methods and Procedure for Process Analysis</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Four analysis phases:</strong> Identify processes, record them and present and evaluate them correctly, completely and uniformly</li>
<li><strong>Interview method:</strong> Surveys with managers and employees familiar with the processes about current working methods and tools used</li>
<li><strong>Workshop method:</strong> Impulse workshops with precise objectives for department-related projects and the project participants involved</li>
<li><strong>Questionnaire method:</strong> Relevant analysis aid for IT managers in the company during quantitative process analysis</li>
<li><strong>Workplace analysis method:</strong> Useful for us as external consultants as a review of current responsibilities and individual activities in the process</li>
</ul>
<p>The methodology is well suited for workplace-related process optimisations and can be individually extended for company-wide optimisation.</p>
<h2>Process Analysis for Innovative Shopping Experiences in All Industries</h2>
<p>The findings of the process analysis produce all aspects with which your online shop reaches customers from manufacturing and processing industries, the fashion sector and the lifestyle segment. Market relevance with a fast, simple and understandable product offering is decisive for success in the automotive industry, furniture and machine builders, agribusiness or education and healthcare sectors.</p>
<h2>Process Analysis by Hob by Horse for Better Target Group Alignment</h2>
<p>One analysis goal can be, among others, to determine target group appeal in B2B trading and improve shopping experiences for specialist customers. In B2C, it makes little sense to constantly chase new trends. Better are updates for simple shop navigation and customer-friendly order processing. Process analysis helps extend the existing shop system with interfaces when optimisation is needed or add additional automated processes.</p>
<p><em>Would you like to start a process analysis now? Arrange a consultation appointment with Hob by Horse by telephone or briefly describe the problem in an <a href="mailto:info@hob-by-horse.de">email</a>!</em></p>
</div></div>
</Base>
